A survey of the product catalogues of the scientific instrument manufacturers will provide an overview of the available instruments. In hands on practice, the students will learn to work with the instruments, know how to properly handle them, and know how to conduct and demonstrate experiments.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give knowledge and practical skills to carry out gymnasium laboratory works and demonstrations.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the student will: 1) have an overview of the leading companies supplying instruments for physics demonstrations, laboratory experiments and practical applications; be able to evaluate these instruments based on the needs of the high school curriculum and on the necessity of teaching in practice;  2) know the empirical principles behind these scientific instruments;  3) be able to conduct demonstrations and explain the results within the framework of of the high school core and elective classes;  4) be able to calibrate the instruments.
